00:00:48.219 --> 00:00:52.350
this cynching screw built into the filter
holder. And what's great about this system

00:00:52.350 --> 00:00:56.149
is it allows you to use our comprehensive
line of filters made specifically for the

00:00:56.149 --> 00:01:01.260
GoPro. This is a circular polarizer--we used
this for our time lapse as well--you just

00:01:01.260 --> 00:01:07.600
screw it onto the filter holder. And what
a circular polarizer does is it allows you,

00:01:07.600 --> 00:01:15.260
by simply turning the front element, to block
out reflections and glare. So, for instance,

00:01:15.270 --> 00:01:19.820
if you were shooting, say, water, and you
wanted to shoot through the reflection and

00:01:19.820 --> 00:01:23.640
see what was underneath, you would just adjust
this until you knocked out that reflection

00:01:23.640 --> 00:01:27.800
and you could see down below. So, like if
you were shooting goldfish in a pond or something

00:01:27.800 --> 00:01:32.920
this would be a great tool. It's also a great
tool to reduce glare off objects, say for

00:01:32.920 --> 00:01:39.920
instance some big silver object that may be
